      <task xml:id="PA-dotproduct-angle">
        <statement>
          <p>
            When we look at vectors drawn with the same initial point, as you have done with the vectors in <xref ref="vec2Dblank"/>, we can consider the angle between two vectors to be the <em>smaller</em> angle formed by looking at them. This results in an angle between <m>0</m> and <m>\pi</m> if we measure in radians or between <m>0^{\circ}</m> and <m>180^{\circ}</m> if we measure in degrees. Rather than measuring the angles between the vectors you've drawn in <xref ref="vec2Dblank"/> precisely, classify the angle between the pairs of vectors in the table in <xref ref="PA-dotproduct-compute" text="type-local"/> by writing acute, right, or obtuse in the <q>Angle Classification</q> column.
          </p>
        </statement>
        <answer>
